cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and the use of network embedding for detecting lexical relations among distributionally similar words. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) and semantic similarity (SI), which makes cs.IR and cs.SI possible sub-categories.
